#: src/natcap/invest/urban_mental_health/urban_mental_health.py:24
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The InVEST Urban Mental Health model estimates the impacts of nature\n"
"    exposure, and more specifically residential greenness, on mental health.\n"
"    Residential nature exposure is defined as the average NDVI within a\n"
"    distance of a residence that benefits human mental health. The mental\n"
"    health model calculates the preventable mental disorder cases at the pixel\n"
"    level, based on the selected urban greening scenario.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: src/natcap/invest/urban_mental_health/urban_mental_health.py:35
msgid "Urban Mental Health"
msgstr ""

#: src/natcap/invest/urban_mental_health/urban_mental_health.py:58
msgid "Map of the area over which to run the model. Ideally, this vector should contain non-overlapping administrative units. The AOI must be smaller than the raster inputs by at least the search radius to ensure correct edge pixel calculation, as InVEST will buffer your AOI by the `search_radius` to determine the processing area. Final outputs will be clipped to this AOI."
